Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the @Carrot{3}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into
roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Pop the carrots onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @Flat Leaf Parsley{1%bunch}(roughly chopped).

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a #medium bowl{}, add the @British Chicken Thighs{3} and
@Roasted Spice and Herb Blend{1%sachet}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, lay the chicken thighs flat in the pan. Fry until browned on each
side and cooked through, ~{13-15%minutes}. Turn every 2-3 minutes.

Once cooked, transfer to your #board{} and allow to rest for a couple of
minutes.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} (with a tight-fitting
lid) on medium heat.

Once hot, add the garlic and @Chermoula Spice Mix{1%sachet}. Fry for ~{30%seconds},
then add the @Couscous{120%g} and stir until coated, ~{1%minute}.

Add the @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g} and @Water for the Couscous{200%ml}. Stir to
combine and bring to the boil.

Pop a #lid{} on the pan and leave to the side, off the heat, for
~{8-10%minutes}, or until ready to serve.

When the carrots have 5 mins remaining, remove the tray from the oven.

Drizzle over the @Honey{1%tbsp} and toss to coat. Return to the oven for the
remaining time.

When everything's ready, fluff up the couscous with a #fork{}. Stir through the
roasted carrots and parsley.

Slice the chicken widthways into 1cm slices.

Share the couscous between your #bowls{} and top with the herby chicken. Drizzle
over the @Greek Style Natural Yoghurt{50.03%g}.

Serve the @Wild Rocket{20%g} alongside drizzled with a little @olive oil{}.

Enjoy!